er chapter on what he calls the ‘rampant state’, that outlines the increasingly authoritarian or ikkyo (one strong) turn of the Abe government in the fifth year of its second term. And he critically addresses the Abe agenda for constitutional revision.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aJapan-Foreign relations-20th century. 0aJapan-Foreign relations-21st century. 0aJapan-Foreign relations-United States. 0aJapan-Politics and government-1989-. 0aUnited States-Foreign relations-Japan. 4aAsian Studies. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 4aJapan. 4aPolitics and Government. 4aPolitics and government. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  achina.  acorruption.  adiplomacy.  anorth korea.  aokinawa.  arussia.  avassalage to usa.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311060672040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781898823728?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781898823728423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781898823728/original  a978-3-11-060672-0  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK